t cert/key and CA cert into spawned agent Jobs when the new\n109\t     `job-kafka-client-cert-secret` and `job-kafka-ca-cert-secret` executor config values are both\n110\t     set â€” projects three read-only (0440) secret files at `/client-cert/file`, `/client-key/file`,\n111\t     `/server-cert/file`. When neither or only one is set, spawned Jobs are unchanged (plaintext-Kafka\n112\t     deployments unaffected).\n113\t   ```\n114\t   If a `## Unreleased` section already exists, append the bullet instead of adding a second heading.\n115\t</requirements>\n116\t\n117\t<constraints>\n118\t- The three mount paths (`/client-cert/file`, `/client-key/file`, `/server-cert/file`), the three secret item keys (`user.crt`, `user.key`, `ca.crt`), the projected file name `file`, and the secret `DefaultMode` `0440` (decimal 288) are FROZEN â€” they mirror the executor-deployment's own cert mounts and the `agent.kafkaCertVolumes` chart helper. Do NOT change them.\n119\t- Both-or-neither: if only one of the two secret names is set, add NO cert volumes or mounts â€” identical to the neither-set case. Never half-configure a pod.\n120\t- The default render (neither secret set) must not change: existing job-spawner tests and any golden Job output must still pass unchanged. Append to `Volumes` / `VolumeMounts`, never overwrite (a PVC `agent-data` volume may coexist).\n121\t- The new mounts apply only to the spawned agent container (the Job's first container, `Containers[0]`), consistent with `applySecretEnvFrom` / `applyVolumeMount`.\n122\t- The executor references secrets by NAME only â€” do NOT read, create, sync, or log secret contents. No cert bytes pass through the executor.\n123\t- Do NOT add a per-agent CRD / Config-CR field and do NOT touch `pkg.AgentConfiguration` â€” these are global executor config (already wired in prompt 1).\n124\t- Do NOT wire the Helm chart or config-repo values â€” out of scope.\n125\t- CHANGELOG: additive minor version bump under `## Unreleased`; the maintainer bot cuts the tag per `.maintainer.yaml`.\n126\t- Do NOT commit â€” dark-factory handles git.\n127\t- Existing tests must still pass.\n128\t</constraints>\n129\t\n130\t<verification>\n131\tRun in `/workspace`:\n132\t```\n133\tmake precommit\n134\tgrep -n 'Unreleased' CHANGELOG.md\n135\tgo test -coverprofile=/tmp/cover.out -mod=vendor ./pkg/spawner/... && go tool cover -func=/tmp/cover.out | tail -1\n136\t```\n137\tExpected:\n138\t- `make precommit` exits 0 â€” all Ginkgo specs green including the new both-set / neither-set / only-client-set / only-CA-set cert-mount cases.\n139\t- `grep 'Unreleased' CHANGELOG.md` returns a line.\n140\t- Coverage for `pkg/spawner` stays at or above 80%.\n141\t\n142\tIf `make precommit` exits non-zero, the prompt is NOT done â€” fix and re-run only the failing target until it passes, then run `make precommit` once more.\n143\t</verification>\n144\t\n145\t## Definition of Done\n146\t\n147\t- [ ] `applyKafkaCertVolumes(job *batchv1.Job)` implemented on `*jobSpawner` with the both-or-neither empty-name gate returning early\n148\t- [ ] Called from `SpawnJob` alongside the other post-build mutators, unconditionally (self-gated)\n149\t- [ ] Both-set case: three secret volumes `client-cert`/`client-key`/`server-cert` with keys `user.crt`/`user.key`/`ca.crt` â†’ path `file`, `DefaultMode` 288, and three container mounts at the three frozen paths\n150\t- [ ] Neither-set and each exactly-one-set case: no cert volumes and no cert mounts (Job unchanged)\n151\t- [ ] Table tests cover both-set, neither-set, only-client-set, only-CA-set; all green\n152\t- [ ] `## Unreleased` CHANGELOG entry with a `feat:` bullet describing the cert-mount capability\n153\t- [ ] `make precommit` exits 0\n154\t- [ ] `pkg/spawner` coverage â‰Ą 80%\n155\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_function_iceqd3zlr1k8_2","session_id":"2797b87b-ab8a-4cea-b290-55a29e5d469e","uuid":"9a6d0176-82e4-4e18-a5b8-2c2f61f50d48","timestamp":"2026-07-09T10:42:11.511Z","subagent_type":"da